<br>
Someone compared us to monks.  My first character was a monk (currently 44th level), so I can compare them a little, at least.  First off, monks have the possibility to hit four times per round (plus special attacks and ripostes).  Specifically, they have the BEST chance to hit four times per round, due to their class bonus to Dual Wield and special damage table.  Beastlords only have the possibility to hit twice per round, and our ability to do that is capped lower than a monk's equivalent skill.<br>
<br>
So yes, we'll attack at least two times less per round than a monk, and our attacks do have a higher possibility of missing, since monks (along with warriors, etc) have the best chance, per swing, to hit in the game.<br>
<br>
But trust me, if that monk hasn't turned off &quot;My Misses&quot;, he's feeling pretty bad, too.  Monks miss a TON, they just get more chances than anyone else.<br>
<br>
